President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of New Hampshire due to a severe storm and snowstorm that occurred on October 29-30, 2011. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas of Hillsborough and Rockingham counties. The federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, emergency protective measures, and hazard mitigation measures. Albert Lewis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact FEMA.